---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { HandbookBoot } from "../components/HandbookBoot";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Tonet Handbook"
  description="Tonet handbook: complete public documentation for users, operators, and contributors."
  page="handbook"
>
  <main class="section pt-10">
    <h1 class="mb-2 text-balance text-4xl" id="handbook-h1">Public handbook</h1>
    <p class="lead" id="handbook-lead">
      This page centralizes expanded project documentation: use cases, utility references, product evolution, and future implementation tracks.
    </p>

    <article class="mb-4 card" id="servo">
      <h2 class="mt-0" id="handbook-servo-h">Servo and Tonet</h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed text-[#9aa3b5]" id="handbook-servo-p1"></p>
      <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-[#9aa3b5]" id="handbook-servo-p2"></p>
      <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-[#9aa3b5]" id="handbook-servo-p3"></p>
    </article>

    <article class="mb-4 card">
      <h2 class="mt-0" id="handbook-use-h">Use cases</h2>
      <ul class="leading-relaxed text-[#9aa3b5]">
        <li id="handbook-use-l1">Low-overhead browsing in controlled environments.</li>
        <li id="handbook-use-l2">Educational and R&amp;D contexts where browser internals must stay transparent.</li>
        <li id="handbook-use-l3">Operational deployment where CDN-based release distribution is required.</li>
        <li id="handbook-use-l4">Security-conscious setups that prefer explicit policy-driven behavior.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="mb-4 card">
      <h2 class="mt-0" id="handbook-util-h">Utilities and internal pages</h2>
      <ul class="leading-relaxed text-[#9aa3b5]">
        <li id="handbook-util-l1">
          <code class="rounded bg-white/[0.06] px-1">tonet://settings</code>: language, theme, update policy, system toggles.
        </li>
        <li id="handbook-util-l2">
          <code class="rounded bg-white/[0.06] px-1">tonet://downloads</code>: page fetch and local save activity.
        </li>
        <li id="handbook-util-l3">
          <code class="rounded bg-white/[0.06] px-1">tonet://history</code>: visit timeline and data management hooks.
        </li>
        <li id="handbook-util-l4">
          <code class="rounded bg-white/[0.06] px-1">tonet://new-tab</code>: shortcuts and search integration.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="mb-4 card">
      <h2 class="mt-0" id="handbook-recent-h">Recent changes</h2>
      <p class="text-[#9aa3b5]" id="handbook-recent-p">
        Recent work focuses on Servo integration foundations, improved policy surfaces, update flow hardening, and stronger CI/document
        reproducibility. Full version notes are tracked in the changelog section after each release.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="mb-4 card">
      <h2 class="mt-0" id="handbook-future-h">Future implementation tracks</h2>
      <ul class="leading-relaxed text-[#9aa3b5]">
        <li id="handbook-fut-l1">Broader selector/layout support for improved compatibility.</li>
        <li id="handbook-fut-l2">Expanded cross-platform packaging and installer parity.</li>
        <li id="handbook-fut-l3">More complete test matrices for conformance and regressions.</li>
        <li id="handbook-fut-l4">Incremental performance and memory budget enforcement.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h2 class="mt-0" id="handbook-compare-h">Comparison notes</h2>
      <p class="text-[#9aa3b5]" id="handbook-compare-p">
        Tonet is intentionally narrower than mature browsers like Chrome and Brave. It targets clarity, policy control, and operational determinism first. See <a
          class="text-tonet-link hover:underline"
          href="/compare.html">Compare</a> for a concise positioning summary.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>

  <p class="mx-auto max-w-[1120px] px-6 pb-10 text-center text-[#9aa3b5]">
    <a class="text-tonet-link hover:underline" id="handbook-footer" href="/docs.html">Back to docs portal</a>
  </p>
  <HandbookBoot client:load />
</BaseLayout>
